  "prompt": "What are good examples of websites built using Adobe ColdFusion?",
  "response": "Adobe ColdFusion is a powerful web application development platform that has been used to build a variety of websites. Here are some examples of notable websites that have been built using ColdFusion:\n\n1. **NASA**: The official website of NASA has used ColdFusion for various applications to manage and present its extensive data and media.\n\n2. **The Mayo Clinic**: This leading medical center uses ColdFusion to provide information and services to patients and healthcare professionals.\n\n3. **MarketWatch**: A financial news website that provides real-time stock market quotes, business news, and analysis. ColdFusion helps in delivering timely data and interactive features.\n\n4. **Adobe**: Not surprisingly, Adobe itself uses ColdFusion for various parts of its website, including its customer service portals.\n\n5. **BMW USA**: The American website for BMW leverages ColdFusion for its interactive features and rich media content.\n\n6. **The Weather Channel**: Known for its comprehensive weather forecasting, The Weather Channel uses ColdFusion to manage dynamic content delivery.\n\n7. **Gamespot**: A popular gaming news and review website, Gamespot utilizes ColdFusion to handle its user interactions and vast content database.\n\nThese examples showcase ColdFusion\u2019s capability to handle large-scale, high-traffic websites with robust functionality and dynamic content.",
